Source: Reuters Institute Digital News Report 2025, p.50',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "use_cases" VALUES (320,'Reuters Institute Digital News Report 2025','Curated','https://www.digitalnewsreport.org/','2026-05-09T14:43:55.404890+00:00','AI-powered supplementary analyses ','Clarín','Argentina','2025-06','https://www.digitalnewsreport.org/',NULL,'Organisation: Clarín
Country: Argentina
Argentina''s Clarín newspaper now offers users both a text-to-audio option and UalterAI, a tool offering a range of supplementary analyses ranging from key bullet points and highlighted quotes, to key figures, a glossary, and a list of Frequently Asked Questions.
Source: Reuters Institute Digital News Report 2025, p.50',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "use_cases" VALUES (321,'Reuters Institute Digital News Report 2025','Curated','https://www.digitalnewsreport.org/','2026-05-09T14:43:55.405008+00:00','The Independent launches ''Bulletin'' — AI-generated news summaries for younger readers','The Independent','United Kingdom','2025-06','https://www.digitalnewsreport.org/',NULL,'Organisation: The Independent
Country: United Kingdom
The Independent (UK) has launched a new digital news service called Bulletin – advertised as ''News for Seriously Busy People'' – which uses Google''s generative AI service Gemini to create article summaries overseen by journalists, aimed at younger readers.
Source: Reuters Institute Digital News Report 2025, p.50',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "use_cases" VALUES (322,'Reuters Institute Digital News Report 2025','Curated','https://www.digitalnewsreport.org/','2026-05-09T14:43:55.405108+00:00','Launches generative AI tool to answer user questions from article archive','The Washington Post','United States','2025-06','https://www.digitalnewsreport.org/',NULL,'Organisation: Washington Post
Country: United States
